**Special Containment Procedures:** All SCP Foundation Sites and personnel are to imperatively transfer any and all information regarding Daniel Asheworth's whereabouts to O5-9. Withholding of such information is considered treason and is going to be punished by immediate termination.

As SCP-6120 has already transpired, its containment is both impossible and unnecessary. To ensure the safety of all personnel following it, however, [[[secure-facility-dossier-site-120|Site-120]]] is currently undergoing a lockdown to properly catch and neutralize the leaders of the attackers,[[footnote]] Daniel Asheworth, Jessie Rivera, Jeremy Cornwell, and Ailbié Tier'ney. [[/footnote]] should they still remain within its premises.

**Description:** SCP-6120 was a military and thaumaturgic raid on Site-120 organized by the recently formed anti-Foundation rebellion.[[footnote]] A group focused on overthrowing O5-9, the current Administrator, in an attempt to take over the organization. Made up of a [[[somewhere-out-there|rogue part of GoI-120 ("Triumviraté")]]] and the remaining parts of PoI-5936 ("Damien Nowak")'s cult and followers following [[[SCP-5672|his death]]], lead by Daniel Asheworth, an ex-Foundation personnel and [[[for-crimes-uncommitted|traitor]]]. [[/footnote]] Having happened on 06/09/1985, the event itself was not anomalous in any way[[footnote]] Eparch class objects are those that aren't necessarily anomalous themselves, but somehow relate to the anomalous. [[/footnote]] -- however, both the attackers and the methods they used to accomplish their deeds were. Utilizing thaumaturgy, ontokinetics, and the help of Fae (//Homo sapiens sidhe//) and [[[SCP-1000|Children of the Night]]] (//Homo sapiens noctis//), their main purpose was the apprehension of [[[SCP-5292|SCP-5292-2]]][[footnote]] A humanoid possessing extremely complex knowledge regarding numerous thaumaturgic practices. [[/footnote]] for the furthering of their goals via the usage of its knowledge.

[[div id="blink-bar"]]
Having successfully done so, in the process, the group caused 100% of personnel within the building to enter a thaumaturgically-induced coma-state. The recovery of them to ensure their proper recovery into health is still pending review from the desk of O5-9. The
[[/div]]

